<br>
With gear a 60 wiz in Luclin is a damage machine compared to melee.  In pre-luclin zones a properly equiped wiz can even hold their own in an exp group now.  I do think non-uber 60 wizards fall behind non-uber 60 melees in exp groups and 59- wizards are kinda pathetic.<br>
<br>
I have no problem with wizards requiring gear to be balanced with melee.  I think that is the way it should have been from the start.  There really wasn't much difference between an uber wiz and a not-so-uber wizard.  Now those who have put the time and effort into this game and have taken on the challenges of the high-end game can reap the rewards.<br>
<br>
With a more abundance of FT items, focus gear, increased mana regen and aa abilities the game really has changed for wizards and casters in general.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/uandylious99.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Andylious99</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady Vox</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/18/02 2:33:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=386.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All you non wizards visiting here...</span><hr size=1> AA ability &gt; gears  <p><center> <image src="http://members.aol.com/awwandiiishon/images/sigz1.jpg"> <center/>

