<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What do you think are their strenght? Their weakness?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Wizards have some serious strengths.  Without a wizard a PoH raid would not be possible, high-end mobs would die far far more slowly, porting people from one raid to the next would require a fleet of druids etc.  On top of that you have the obvious weaknesses.  AC of Kleenex (not that AC really matters) strong talent for pissing off mobs (I know all about that one) and unfortunately before AA or without any form of clarity a lower DPS in groups than what a similarly equipped melee would have.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  What use to you see in a wizard in an XP group? In raid situations?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Evac, and with a bard or enchanter fairly effective damage.  <br>
<br>
Unfortunately for wizards/druids/mages and other AE capable people AE groups are more effective, or soloing, than standard melee/healer groups.  I dont get invited to AE (my poison rain does 3 shocks of 540 damage or hits up to 4 targets, shaman AE is a joke) and my buffs don't do much for wizards (I can get most of you close to 255 str though if you ever want to see it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  <br>
<br>
So generally I won't duo with wizards as separate soloing is more effective unless we are after large kills rather than volume of kills.  For killing a big monster shaman + wizard is a pretty mean pair. <p><center><img src="http://cleric.homestead.com/files/mathi.jpg" border="0">
